data.name: label19.Text
data.value:
Select egde or corner to detect. Place tool tip in front of edge. On corners, X will be probed first, then Y. Z will be probed last.
Probe edge a 2nd time on another position to get angle.

data.name: label21.Text
data.value:
Inner contour: Place tool tip inside hole of work piece, almost centered. Z will not moved.
Outside contour: Place tool tip on left side of work piece, as for edge detection

data.name: label12.Text
data.value:
1. Get tool length for 1st tool 2. Use G92 to set Z zero 3. After tool change, just measure tool length again, Z coordinate will then corrected.
After tool length probing: Z will move back to start position
